1
00:01:10,170 --> 00:01:12,171
Duke?

2
00:01:12,173 --> 00:01:14,306
Testin' our accommodations.

3
00:01:14,308 --> 00:01:16,675
Well, sorry to bother you,
but sam verdreaux called.

4
00:01:16,677 --> 00:01:18,444
He sounded good and sauced,
but he wants us to know

5
00:01:18,446 --> 00:01:20,179
That he heard
some kind of a bang.

6
00:01:20,181 --> 00:01:22,114
Like a car backfired?

7
00:01:22,116 --> 00:01:25,751
Or a bang like tommy anderson
finally shot his wife?

8
00:01:25,753 --> 00:01:27,686
He didn't specify.

9
00:01:27,688 --> 00:01:29,688
But sam's the only one
that called it in,

10
00:01:29,690 --> 00:01:30,722
So I didn't want to overreact.

11
00:01:30,724 --> 00:01:32,424
No.

12
00:01:32,426 --> 00:01:34,493
You were right to get me, linda.

13
00:01:36,696 --> 00:01:38,730
Never know with this damn place.

14
00:01:46,639 --> 00:01:48,640
You off to the game
today, big jim?

15
00:01:48,642 --> 00:01:50,676
No, I'm sitting this
one out, actually.

16
00:01:50,678 --> 00:01:53,112
Aw. I thought
the whole town council

17
00:01:53,114 --> 00:01:56,715
Always rode
that stupid float together.

18
00:01:56,717 --> 00:01:58,851
Working the lot today,

19
00:01:58,853 --> 00:02:01,220
So the guys...

20
00:02:01,222 --> 00:02:02,454
Let me sit this one out.

21
00:02:02,456 --> 00:02:05,124
Heavy is the head
that wears many hats.

22
00:02:05,126 --> 00:02:07,826
I'm not sure that's quite
how that one goes.

23
00:02:07,828 --> 00:02:10,896
We're having a big sale
on our pre-owns.

24
00:02:12,465 --> 00:02:15,334
Hoping we're a little busier
than here, no offense.

25
00:02:15,336 --> 00:02:17,669
Sunday mornings have been brutal
since they opened that denny's

26
00:02:17,671 --> 00:02:22,474
I'll take your french toast
any day of the week, rose.

27
00:02:24,777 --> 00:02:26,578
Jim...

28
00:02:26,580 --> 00:02:27,746
What is this?

29
00:02:27,748 --> 00:02:29,515
That's me buying your next vote.

30
00:02:29,517 --> 00:02:31,884
Says the guy
who always runs unopposed.

31
00:02:31,886 --> 00:02:34,520
We're all in this together.

32
00:02:39,893 --> 00:02:42,261
God!

33
00:02:42,263 --> 00:02:44,830
I know, right?

34
00:02:46,634 --> 00:02:49,701
No, you don't.

35
00:02:54,375 --> 00:02:57,442
Angie...
Huh?

36
00:03:00,780 --> 00:03:02,848
I love you.

37
00:03:03,816 --> 00:03:06,685
Yeah.

38
00:03:06,687 --> 00:03:09,755
It's been a fun summer.

39
00:03:12,392 --> 00:03:13,892
Ouch.

40
00:03:13,894 --> 00:03:15,894
Junior, we both
know what this is.

41
00:03:15,896 --> 00:03:18,597
And you go back to
school in a few days.

42
00:03:18,599 --> 00:03:20,933
No, I'm not.
I'm, uh...

43
00:03:20,935 --> 00:03:22,801
