unaccounted for,

524
00:34:26,265 --> 00:34:27,531
But it looks like

525
00:34:27,533 --> 00:34:30,834
Chester's mill...

526
00:34:30,836 --> 00:34:32,836
Lost 12 of her own today.

527
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:37,841
Rose:
Duke...

528
00:34:37,843 --> 00:34:39,476
What the hell is going on?

529
00:34:39,478 --> 00:34:40,811
Isn't it obvious?

530
00:34:40,813 --> 00:34:41,845
We're under attack.

531
00:34:41,847 --> 00:34:43,547
Duke: Nobody knows
a damn thing,

532
00:34:43,549 --> 00:34:45,515
So there's no point
in spreading any rumors.

533
00:34:45,517 --> 00:34:46,783
Please,
our daughter is sick.

534
00:34:46,785 --> 00:34:48,418
We need to get her
to a real doctor.

535
00:34:48,420 --> 00:34:50,787
I mean, even if they can't
knock that wall down,

536
00:34:50,789 --> 00:34:52,789
They can still airlift
her out of here.

537
00:34:52,791 --> 00:34:54,524
Well, I don't know, but
if those eggheads out there

538
00:34:54,526 --> 00:34:55,826
Can drop a car on mars,

539
00:34:55,828 --> 00:34:57,527
They sure as hell
can figure this out, too.

540
00:34:57,529 --> 00:35:00,597
When everybody gets home
tonight,

541
00:35:00,599 --> 00:35:02,432
I want you to check
on your neighbors,

542
00:35:02,434 --> 00:35:07,471
And if anybody needs anything,
you know where to find me.

543
00:35:37,535 --> 00:35:39,503
Hey, angie.

544
00:35:39,505 --> 00:35:40,604
Help!

545
00:35:40,606 --> 00:35:44,541
Somebody help me!
Somebody help me!

546
00:35:44,543 --> 00:35:47,444
Stop it, quiet down, stop.
Oh, god, please help me!

547
00:35:47,446 --> 00:35:49,479
Stop!

548
00:35:49,481 --> 00:35:52,349
Save your voice, babe.

549
00:35:52,351 --> 00:35:54,484
Okay? No one can hear us
all the way down here.

550
00:35:54,486 --> 00:35:56,553
Down?

551
00:35:56,555 --> 00:36:00,490
My dad's old fallout shelter.

552
00:36:00,492 --> 00:36:03,660
He's always been a little
paranoid about security,

553
00:36:03,662 --> 00:36:07,430
But... You're safe now.

554
00:36:09,367 --> 00:36:11,434
What are you talking about?

555
00:36:11,436 --> 00:36:13,537
I finally
figured it out--

556
00:36:13,539 --> 00:36:15,539
Why you were acting
so strange this morning.

557
00:36:15,541 --> 00:36:17,841
It's all connected.

558
00:36:19,678 --> 00:36:22,512
I know how this
must look, but...

559
00:36:22,514 --> 00:36:23,613
I swear, in the long run,

560
00:36:23,615 --> 00:36:26,449
You're gonna
thank me for this.

561
00:36:28,886 --> 00:36:31,421
Oh, my god,
you've lost your mind.

562
00:36:31,423 --> 00:36:33,290
No, no.

563
00:36:33,292 --> 00:36:35,225
I'm the only person
who understands

564
00:36:35,227 --> 00:36:37,427
What's really going
on around here.

565
00:36:38,396 --> 00:36:40,764
All I ask for...

566
00:36:40,766 --> 00:36:42,832
Is patience.

567
00:36:46,604 --> 00:36:50,540
Let go of me!
Let go of me!

568
00:36:50,542 --> 00:36:52,943
Let me out of here!

569
00:36:52,945 --> 00:36:55,679
Get me out, get me out!

570
00:36:55,681 --> 00:36:58,848
Junior! Junior!

571
00:37:06,657 --> 00:37:08,725
Man:
Junior.

572
00:37:15,700 --> 00:37:17,667
Dad.

573
00:37:17,669 --> 00:37:20,470
Heard you on the radio.
It sounded

574
00:37:20,472 --> 00:37:21,671
Like we might need
the old shelter,

575
00:37:21,673 --> 00:37:23,974
But it's completely flooded.

576
00:37:23,976 --> 00:37:26,276
Oh, tha-that's the least
of our worries.

577
00:37:26,278 --> 00:37:28,511
All that matters
is you're okay.

578
00:37:28,513 --> 00:37:31,648
Whatever this is,
I want to help.

579
00:37:31,650 --> 00:37:34,451
I appreciate that,
but you got school...

580
00:37:34,453 --> 00:37:36,586
School is out there,
I'm here,

581
00:37:36,588 --> 00:37:39,456
And I want to help.

582
00:38:04,715 --> 00:38:07,784
♪

583
00:38:11,756 --> 00:38:13,923
Honey, are you home?

584
00:38:19,997 --> 00:38:21,998
How do you guys have power?

585
00:38:25,403 --> 00:38:28,905
Big jim convinced my husband
it would be a tax write-off

586
00:38:28,907 --> 00:38:31,308
When we moved in here.

587
00:38:31,310 --> 00:38:32,609
That's peter behind you.

588
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:57,033
You must think I'm an idiot.

589
00:39:02,406 --> 00:39:04,474
Wha-what do, what do you mean?

590
00:39:06,977 --> 00:39:08,978
Journalist who doesn't know
what's going on

591
00:39:08,980 --> 00:39:10,480
Under her own nose.

592
00:39:15,052 --> 00:39:17,554
I'm sure
the whole town's thinking it.

593
00:39:20,725 --> 00:39:24,427
My husband isn't here
because he's having an affair.

594
00:39:37,675 --> 00:39:40,143
They don't know him like I do.

595
00:39:40,145 --> 00:39:42,412
He'll turn up, you'll see.

596
00:39:44,382 --> 00:39:47,617
I can't wait to meet him.

597
00:39:51,856 --> 00:39:53,690
Come on, I'll give you
the nickel tour.

598
00:40:06,704 --> 00:40:10,907
I was supposed to be
with rusty today, at the game.

599
00:40:10,909 --> 00:40:14,177
Told him if we were ever
going to afford a honeymoon,

600
00:40:14,179 --> 00:40:17,046
We both had to put
in more overtime.

601
00:40:23,188 --> 00:40:25,455
Why chester's mill?

602
00:40:28,459 --> 00:40:30,527
Why us?

603
00:40:32,096 --> 00:40:34,164
Maybe we're being punished.

604
00:40:35,566 --> 00:40:37,567
Sorry?

605
00:40:37,569 --> 00:40:39,636
You're good police, linda.

606
00:40:41,071 --> 00:40:44,073
But...

607
00:40:44,075 --> 00:40:46,209
There's a lot I've tried
to protect you from

608
00:40:46,211 --> 00:40:48,945
About this place.

609
00:40:48,947 --> 00:40:50,513
Like what?

610
00:41:03,894 --> 00:41:08,131
Little over a year ago,
I was approached about...

611
00:41:14,638 --> 00:41:16,039
Duke...

612
00:41:16,041 --> 00:41:17,040
My chest.

613
00:41:17,042 --> 00:41:18,908
Duke, is it your pacemaker?

614
00:41:19,911 --> 00:41:21,044
Duke, don't!

615
00:41:21,046 --> 00:41:23,546
Duke, duke!

616
00:41:23,548 --> 00:41:25,548
Help!

617
00:41:25,550 --> 00:41:27,550
Officer down! Officer down!

618
00:41:27,552 --> 00:41:29,052
Help!

619
00:41:29,054 --> 00:41:30,520
Duke, come on,
stay with me, duke.

620
00:41:30,522 --> 00:41:32,055
Duke, stay with me.

621
00:41:32,057 --> 00:41:33,056
Help u...!

622
00:41:33,058 --> 00:41:36,726
♪

623
00:41:36,728 --> 00:41:45,068
Man:
Move it, move it, move it.

624
00:41:45,070 --> 00:41:46,503
Male reporter: <i>We've spoken</i>
<i>with the government,</i>

625
00:41:46,505 --> 00:41:48,171
<i>Law enforcement, the military.</i>

626
00:41:48,173 --> 00:41:50,840
<i>No one has any idea</i>
<i>what's going on here.</i>

627
00:41:50,842 --> 00:41:52,909
<i>The closest I can come</i>
<i>to an answer is to share...</i>

628
00:41:52,911 --> 00:41:54,110
Female reporter: <i>...Is to share</i>
<i>with you the words</i>

629
00:41:54,112 --> 00:41:57,747
<i>He told us, and I quote,</i>
<i>"this is an unparalleled..."</i>

630
00:41:57,749 --> 00:42:01,284
Female reporter:
<i>"...An unparalleled event</i>
<i>in human history."</i>

631
00:42:01,286 --> 00:42:04,587
<i>Those are not words of comfort</i>
<i>not the nation or the world.</i>

632
00:42:04,589 --> 00:42:07,657
<i>Certainly not to the people of</i>
<i>chester's mill who appear to be</i>
<i>trapped.</i>

633
00:42:14,198 --> 00:42:17,734
